The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Chirag have a battle on hand
                                                                                                                       7                                      Chirag have a battle on hand
                      
	Pune: Winless Pune FC will be desperate to come out from the rut when they take on a depleted Chirag United in a round four I-League match at the Shiv Chhatrapati Sports Complex here on Saturday.         
	Down with fever and hospitalised in Calcutta, Chirag United coach Subrata Bhattacharya has not accompanied the team which will also miss four key players.         
	The Chirag line-up will be without defender Arnab Mondal, midfielder Denson Devadas, who has opted out of the tie for personal reasons, while midfielder Jeri Zirsanga will sit out because of a double booking and Subhas Chakraborty is injured.         
	Pune FC will be without Brazillian striker Edmar Figuera who has an ankle injury.         
	Coach Derrick Pereira said: Our target is to win and there is no sense in dwelling on the past. Every match is a new start.         
	Pereira said Figueras absence would not be missed.         
	Our opponents have a very good strikers in Junior Elijah and Joshimar. They will be a team who will certainly going to test the defence.         
	Pune FC have been playing well, but have been denied a win owing to their finishing up front.         
	Our midfield and strikers need to combine well and convert the chances we create, the coach said.                                                                                                                     
